		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_43592957" name="comment_link_43592957" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3703395&amp;cid=43592957" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(43592957)" >Four ways to profit</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_43592957" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 43592957); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~onyxruby">onyxruby</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~onyxruby">(118189)</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_43592957">		 &lt;<a href="mailto:%7Bonyxruby%7D+%7Bat%7D+%7Bcomcast.net%7D">{onyxruby} {at} {comcast.net}</a>&gt;
		on Tuesday April 30, 2013 @02:18PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3703395&amp;cid=43592957">#43592957</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_43592957"><p>You can profit from bitcoin in four different ways:</p><p>1. Have a special asic rig that is custom made for mining bitcoins.<br>2. Have a botnet that you put to work mining bitcoins using other peoples electricity.<br>3. Speculate in bitcoins and bet that they will go up or down in value.<br>4. Hack someone else that has bitcoins.</p><p>Two out of the four ways to make profits with bitcoins are illegal and one of the others is often accompanied by illegal activity (DOS) to manipulate the exchanges to try to force the value up or down. It's been a while since you could mine them on your own and come out ahead on electricity versus bitcoin value. Perhaps there are some good reasons bitcoins have a shady reputation?</p></div>
	</div>

